        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer876213166" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3817428211079367375">Christopher Hitchens was my 5-star author hero. Everything he wrote I had to ration how much I read at a time so I could savour his writing, his pronouncements, his humour and his wisdom. This book was but a pale shadow of his others and I couldn&apos;t finish it. I may one day pick it up again.<br/><br/>Although Hitchens is often the star of his own books, he is able to put himself to one side to concentrate on the subject. Unfortunately in this one he is not just the star, but the elevated hero, and great as</span>
  <span id="freeText3817428211079367375" style="display:none">Christopher Hitchens was my 5-star author hero. Everything he wrote I had to ration how much I read at a time so I could savour his writing, his pronouncements, his humour and his wisdom. This book was but a pale shadow of his others and I couldn't finish it. I may one day pick it up again.<br /><br />Although Hitchens is often the star of his own books, he is able to put himself to one side to concentrate on the subject. Unfortunately in this one he is not just the star, but the elevated hero, and great as a writer he might have been, as a person he was no less flawed than the rest of us. Perhaps more so, perhaps that is what made him so interesting.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="3817428211079367375" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
